        <p><strong>PARC</strong> (<strong>P</strong>alo <strong>A</strong>lto <strong>R</strong>esearch <strong>C</strong>enter Incorporated), formerly <strong>Xerox PARC</strong>, is a research and development company in Palo Alto, California, with a distinguished reputation for its contributions to information technology and hardware systems.</p>
        <p>Founded in 1970 as a division of <strong>Xerox Corporation</strong>, PARC has been responsible for such well known and important developments as laser printing, Ethernet, the modern personal computer, graphical user interface (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('GUI', 'IT'); ?>) and desktop paradigm, object-oriented programming, ubiquitous computing, amorphous silicon applications, and advancing very-large-scale-integration (VLSI) for semiconductors.</p>
